[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Stops garden and vineyard seed counts from slowly bleeding dry. Vanilla gives you fewer seeds back than you plant, so every harvest is a loss over time — this mod aims to keep at least a 1:1 ratio and usually ends up net-positive.[/size]

[size=3][b]Per-garden toggles[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Player Gardens[/b] — the beds you tend yourself.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zombie Gardens[/b] — beds worked by zombie farmhands.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Refugee Gardens[/b] — beds inside the refugee camp (Game of Crone DLC).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zombie Vineyards[/b] — vine-growing beds worked by zombies.[/size]
[/list]
[size=3]Each is an independent toggle, so you can equalise some and leave others vanilla.[/size]

[size=3][b]Balance knobs[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Seed output boost[/b] — slider that nudges the potential seed yield above 1:1 across all enabled garden types. Turn up if you want a seed surplus.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zombie-garden and zombie-vineyard waste output[/b] — optional. Adds the waste item (plant fibre / rotten grape) to their harvest pool. Matches how player gardens work.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Rain grow-speed boost[/b] — when it's raining, plants grow noticeably faster. Off by default. Stacks with any other speed mods.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3]No unlock gating — the mod applies the moment a garden bed or vineyard runs a harvest cycle.[/size]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/76]Where's Ma' Veggies[/url] — harvest every garden plot of the same type simultaneously (requires the Farmer perk).[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] — includes per-type garden speedups for player / zombie / refugee gardens.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multiplier on crop drops. Stacks with The Seed Equalizer's output boost.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory so harvested crops flow into every workstation.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

